1
00:00:01,335 --> 00:00:02,775
<i>Previously on</i> The Magicians...

2
00:00:10,911 --> 00:00:13,278
Your new lady Centurion!

3
00:00:18,318 --> 00:00:20,719
You said you heard
voices from other worlds.

4
00:00:21,021 --> 00:00:23,547
You hearing something? A signal?

5
00:00:27,461 --> 00:00:30,158
Professor? Did the
signal make you do that?

6
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:34,899
<i>He loved you.</i>

7
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:37,213
Why would I want to take
that away from you now?

8
00:00:37,237 --> 00:00:38,603
That would be so cruel.

9
00:00:40,474 --> 00:00:42,394
Do you really think I didn't
know there was more?

10
00:00:44,077 --> 00:00:45,670
<i>What was I supposed to do, huh?</i>

11
00:00:47,314 --> 00:00:49,306
Demand that he only love me?

12
00:00:49,383 --> 00:00:51,545
"Dark King" is a little generic

13
00:00:51,618 --> 00:00:52,950
as villain names go. Mmm.

14
00:00:53,053 --> 00:00:54,681
Wouldn't you say? I have notes.

15
00:00:54,755 --> 00:00:56,519
Although he is
somewhat effective.

16
00:00:56,590 --> 00:00:58,183
Everyone seems terrified of him.

17
00:00:58,258 --> 00:01:00,250
Eliot, Taker! Back up.

18
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:08,535
You all right?

19
00:01:11,038 --> 00:01:15,339
Death is so simple and
life is so complicated.

20
00:01:17,044 --> 00:01:18,103
I know.

21
00:01:20,714 --> 00:01:22,774
I think I almost
fucked the Dark King.

22
00:01:23,116 --> 00:01:25,176
Are you familiar with the
Harmonic Convergence?

23
00:01:25,252 --> 00:01:28,279
A rare and powerful
astrological occurrence.

24
00:01:28,388 --> 00:01:29,720
A magnifier of magic.

25
00:01:29,790 --> 00:01:30,883
How bad will it be?

26
00:01:30,958 --> 00:01:33,291
Death toll in the millions.
Maybe much higher.

27
00:01:33,393 --> 00:01:35,259
How can we stop it? You can't.

28
00:01:35,362 --> 00:01:36,955
<i>I repeat, ward break.</i>

29
00:01:41,568 --> 00:01:42,568
<i>Hedge witches.</i>

30
00:01:42,636 --> 00:01:44,798
<i>They're used to crumbs
and, yes, ambient is low.</i>

31
00:01:44,905 --> 00:01:46,082
<i>But you know what amplifies it?</i>

32
00:01:46,106 --> 00:01:47,301
<i>Cooperative magic.</i>

33
00:01:47,407 --> 00:01:48,739
<i>We tell everyone,</i>

34
00:01:48,809 --> 00:01:51,904
and we all do the same
thing at the same time.

35
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:57,717
<i>And I thought that if I took on
more power and more responsibility,</i>

36
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:00,553
<i>that I'd want heroin less.</i>

37
00:02:00,621 --> 00:02:02,283
<i>When I thought I'd relapsed,</i>

38
00:02:03,156 --> 00:02:04,488
I was relieved.

39
00:02:10,097 --> 00:02:12,931
So, uh, I've been
clean for a year.

40
00:02:14,401 --> 00:02:15,401
Barely.

41
00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:18,029
Thanks, but, uh, maybe hold that

42
00:02:19,272 --> 00:02:22,140
'cause I've been jonesing hard.

43
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:28,448
Well, uh, I'm a Hedge.

44
00:02:29,449 --> 00:02:32,942
You know, before we helped
save magic, we got a shit deal, right?

45
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:35,182
Well, there was a
blood worm scare,

46
00:02:35,288 --> 00:02:37,328
so the Library gave a lot
of Hedges the Reed's Mark.

47
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:41,352
Get a mark, you're magically
castrated until they take it off.

48
00:02:41,695 --> 00:02:43,506
And the Library's
imploding, they can't fix it,

49
00:02:43,530 --> 00:02:46,432
and the marked ones
are looking at me like,

50
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:50,062
"Hey, bossy pants, you rallied us to
save magic, how about saving us?"

51
00:02:50,671 --> 00:02:53,835
And I found a spell to remove
the marks in a depository,

52
00:02:55,042 --> 00:02:57,477
Only, all of a
sudden, it's gone.

53
00:02:57,544 --> 00:03:01,811
But I know only way to
move something that warded

54
00:03:01,882 --> 00:03:03,783
is to move it through
the Etheric Realm.

55
00:03:04,651 --> 00:03:07,211
Cool. I've heard it's awesome
there. What's the prob?

56
00:03:07,988 --> 00:03:09,354
The prob

57
00:03:11,324 --> 00:03:13,054
is there's only one
way into the Realm.

58
00:03:15,362 --> 00:03:17,194
Anybody heard of "RCH"?

59
00:03:18,799 --> 00:03:20,165
Nickname, "Archie"?

60
00:03:23,804 --> 00:03:24,999
Yup.

61
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:29,810
The way to save every
marked Hedge is to drop acid.

62
00:03:32,279 --> 00:03:33,747
True 12-step conundrum.

63
00:03:40,353 --> 00:03:42,673
I'm assuming you
have the Archie on you?

64
00:03:43,557 --> 00:03:45,185
Call your sponsor, kid.

65
00:03:45,559 --> 00:03:46,720
It'd make sense,

66
00:03:48,595 --> 00:03:52,691
in case somebody here, you know,
gave you permission to jump off the wagon.

67
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:54,729
Sorry MA is so strict.

68
00:03:54,835 --> 00:03:56,235
You met the nice me.

69
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:58,033
Here's the real me.

70
00:03:58,205 --> 00:03:59,298
Fuck off.

71
00:04:04,444 --> 00:04:05,571
What?

72
00:04:08,615 --> 00:04:14,521
Well, I take the "anonymous" part of
Magicians Anonymous very seriously.

73
00:04:14,855 --> 00:04:16,847
So, you quit drinking?

74
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:19,119
Thirty-three days,
six hours, 19 minutes

75
00:04:19,226 --> 00:04:22,719
of skin-peeling,
soul-searing hell ago, yes.

76
00:04:23,563 --> 00:04:25,498
Well, I can relate. As can I,

77
00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:29,095
in regards to the crushing
weight of leadership.

78
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:33,931
I've never seen Archie.

79
00:04:35,342 --> 00:04:36,810
May I?

80
00:04:40,781 --> 00:04:41,781
Why two?

81
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:45,112
In case the first trip's a bust.

82
00:04:45,485 --> 00:04:47,716
Or in case it's fun.

83
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:53,753
I've been dismissive or
downright derisive about Hedges,

84
00:04:53,827 --> 00:04:56,160
and I admit, I was quite wrong,

85
00:04:56,663 --> 00:04:58,632
and I'd like to try
and make, um...

86
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:00,627
Hell, what's the word?

87
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:03,002
Amends. Yeah.

88
00:05:09,376 --> 00:05:10,376
Are you crazy?

89
00:05:11,678 --> 00:05:12,678
I am.

90
00:05:12,779 --> 00:05:14,941
But I am not an addict.

91
00:05:15,015 --> 00:05:17,484
I'm an alcoholic.
Totally different.

92
00:05:18,852 --> 00:05:21,151
So, I will go hunt
down the depository.

93
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,858
You're not going alone.

94
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:41,297
So we know about the
Harmonic Convergence.

95
00:05:41,374 --> 00:05:43,366
The problem is we know
just enough to be useless,

96
00:05:43,476 --> 00:05:46,344
so maybe we find someone
who can see the big picture.

97
00:05:46,847 --> 00:05:49,373
Find? Summon.

98
00:05:50,684 --> 00:05:51,811
A god?

99
00:05:53,954 --> 00:05:55,131
Whoa, you've got
to be kidding me.

100
00:05:55,155 --> 00:05:58,353
Wait. Julia, before you do that,
I think the Library might have...

101
00:05:59,559 --> 00:06:01,585
Penny? I'm fine.

102
00:06:02,896 --> 00:06:05,229
Wow, that is a whole
other level. Jesus.

103
00:06:05,332 --> 00:06:06,823
I thought the patch was working.

104
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,711
Merritt's signal just
keeps getting stronger.

105
00:06:08,735 --> 00:06:12,729
I'm sorry. I can't stay. I'm just no
use until I get this under control.

106
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:14,740
Maybe do the summoning
once I get back?

107
00:06:15,609 --> 00:06:17,043
Let me know if
things get too weird.

108
00:06:17,143 --> 00:06:18,805
Yeah. Same.

109
00:06:25,619 --> 00:06:29,681
The Library has summoned me
about 7,000 times to come work there.

110
00:06:30,290 --> 00:06:31,622
And they also gave me this.

111
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,261
It'll get me in any time I want.

112
00:06:35,729 --> 00:06:37,273
Look, I'll bring back
whatever they have

113
00:06:37,297 --> 00:06:39,061
on the Harmonic
Convergence as fast as I can.

114
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:42,069
Are you sure you'll
be okay? Yeah.

115
00:06:42,369 --> 00:06:44,235
Good luck. You, too.

116
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:50,169
Makes sense the
signal's hitting you harder.

117
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:52,572
I'm starting to actually
hear... A voice?

118
00:06:53,179 --> 00:06:55,205
You, too? Kind of.

119
00:06:55,949 --> 00:06:57,884
I can't make out actual words.

120
00:06:57,951 --> 00:06:59,262
At least, not ones
I can understand.

121
00:06:59,286 --> 00:07:01,278
Is that for me? - No.

122
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:05,120
I think the problem with the first
patch was that it was just a deflector.

123
00:07:05,859 --> 00:07:09,261
The signal is getting bounced off,
but I'm still getting hit by the reverb.

124
00:07:09,329 --> 00:07:12,663
This one should absorb
the sound and kill it.

125
00:07:12,766 --> 00:07:15,201
And if it does, we'll see
what we can gin up for you.

126
00:07:31,217 --> 00:07:32,276
Okay. Mmm.

127
00:07:33,219 --> 00:07:34,517
Better, I think.

128
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:36,455
Uh...

129
00:07:38,591 --> 00:07:39,854
Okay.

130
00:07:45,699 --> 00:07:46,962
What was that?

131
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,433
Where did you go?
I don't remember.

132
00:07:50,503 --> 00:07:52,870
You didn't blip out on purpose?

133
00:07:52,973 --> 00:07:56,171
No, when the pain got so I was
gonna pass out, I just... I just went.

134
00:07:56,276 --> 00:07:57,835
You need a doctor.

135
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:08,079
I'm impressed.

136
00:08:08,788 --> 00:08:10,882
Not with this. It's
dreadful. Sorry.

137
00:08:12,525 --> 00:08:15,495
With your skills as a
Magician. Who trained you?

138
00:08:16,096 --> 00:08:18,096
Well, I just picked up a
little bit here and there.

139
00:08:19,299 --> 00:08:21,859
Clearly not enough, since I
couldn't put a scratch on that Taker.

140
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:23,295
Don't be modest.

141
00:08:24,004 --> 00:08:26,030
You have what it takes
to be quite formidable.

142
00:08:26,139 --> 00:08:27,539
I could use you.

143
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:30,474
Official Court Magician in
Defense of the Kingdom.

144
00:08:30,543 --> 00:08:33,707
You could teach others,
and be taught by me.

145
00:08:35,582 --> 00:08:37,210
I would be honored,

146
00:08:39,119 --> 00:08:40,451
Your Majesty.

147
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:46,458
Hmm.

148
00:08:46,826 --> 00:08:48,590
A different lining, perhaps.

149
00:08:48,695 --> 00:08:49,695
Gray, please.

150
00:08:56,569 --> 00:08:59,596
When we are
alone, it can be Seb.

151
00:09:00,673 --> 00:09:02,005
Well, Seb,

152
00:09:02,776 --> 00:09:04,540
we have a saying
where I come from.

153
00:09:05,011 --> 00:09:07,003
You kinda buried
the lede on the...

154
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:09,914
On the, well...

155
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:12,679
On you.

156
00:09:12,752 --> 00:09:14,084
I didn't mean to deceive you.

157
00:09:15,588 --> 00:09:18,080
Kings have to be very
careful about who to trust.

158
00:09:19,192 --> 00:09:22,321
And also, it can
be a relief to not...

159
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:24,626
Feel the weight of the crown
on your head every second?

160
00:09:25,432 --> 00:09:26,627
You are wise.

161
00:09:27,901 --> 00:09:29,392
But I knew that already.

162
00:09:34,507 --> 00:09:37,204
In any case, settle in,

163
00:09:37,277 --> 00:09:39,906
and we'll get down to the
particulars of your duties later.

164
00:09:40,547 --> 00:09:41,571
All right?

165
00:09:42,282 --> 00:09:45,184
All right, Your Majesty.

166
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:54,206
<i>Ugh, please.</i> ELIOT: <i>What?</i>

167
00:09:54,561 --> 00:09:56,757
If you say his gorgeous
eyes see into your soul,

168
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:58,407
I'm gonna puke all
over your new leggings,

169
00:09:58,431 --> 00:10:00,627
which are quite sharp,
by the way. Thank you.

170
00:10:01,468 --> 00:10:03,562
Legs for days. Thank you.

171
00:10:03,636 --> 00:10:06,902
And I never said his eyes were
gorgeous or that he sees into my soul.

172
00:10:06,973 --> 00:10:08,373
But weirdly, he might.

173
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:11,377
Or he's sucking the soul out of
you because he doesn't have one.

174
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:12,605
Um...

175
00:10:12,712 --> 00:10:13,941
He did save my life.

176
00:10:14,013 --> 00:10:15,106
He's called the Dark King.

177
00:10:15,181 --> 00:10:17,082
You're called
Margo the Destroyer.

178
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:20,245
I was a woman ruling a patriarchy.
My brand had to be overkill.

179
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:22,980
Bottom line, he likes you.

180
00:10:23,089 --> 00:10:24,921
Use that to find out
what he's really about.

181
00:10:29,129 --> 00:10:31,394
I'll see if my fellow
Centurions like to gossip.

182
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:33,592
Then we regroup and decide.

183
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:35,931
Benevolent dictator
by necessity,

184
00:10:36,603 --> 00:10:39,266
or psychopathic
despot by choice?

185
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:41,998
What if he's the latter?
Then I always got his back.

186
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:44,975
Perfect place to bury these.

187
00:11:28,821 --> 00:11:30,915
Zelda, help me, please.

188
00:11:31,057 --> 00:11:32,320
What's going on? Who are they?

189
00:11:32,392 --> 00:11:33,392
Goths.

190
00:11:33,493 --> 00:11:35,928
Like Marilyn Manson? Visigoths.

191
00:11:36,496 --> 00:11:37,725
Oh, Germanic barbarians.

192
00:11:37,830 --> 00:11:40,629
Who always show up at the
absolute worst points in history.

193
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:05,634
Fucking hell.

194
00:12:05,658 --> 00:12:08,025
Oh, sorry. Did you...
Did you want Hades?

195
00:12:08,428 --> 00:12:12,661
I could get word to him,
but, ugh, what a dick.

196
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:14,967
Are you...

197
00:12:15,068 --> 00:12:17,128
I'm Clarion, Goddess of Melody.

198
00:12:17,270 --> 00:12:20,536
Hey, Julia. I've, uh, had my
eye on you for quite a while.

199
00:12:20,673 --> 00:12:22,107
You have? Yeah, yeah.

200
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:23,676
So, you were mortal, right?

201
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:25,921
And then you were one of us, and
now you're back to mortal. Whew.

202
00:12:25,945 --> 00:12:28,505
You're one tough
cookie, Cookie. Thanks?

203
00:12:28,715 --> 00:12:31,617
Yeah, but the way that you're
imagining the Harmonic Convergence

204
00:12:31,718 --> 00:12:34,153
isn't quite enough.

205
00:12:34,254 --> 00:12:35,688
It's so much worse.

206
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:39,582
So, when all the spells cast by
all of the Magicians go haywire,

207
00:12:39,692 --> 00:12:44,426
you're gonna get earthquakes,
fire, drought, starvation, plague.

208
00:12:45,131 --> 00:12:46,429
And then comes cannibalism.

209
00:12:46,499 --> 00:12:47,558
Um...

210
00:12:47,634 --> 00:12:49,068
Is there anything you can do?

211
00:12:49,869 --> 00:12:51,167
I could stop it.

212
00:12:51,504 --> 00:12:52,767
How would that be? Great.

213
00:12:52,872 --> 00:12:55,569
But I'm assuming there's
something you want in return.

214
00:12:58,111 --> 00:13:01,240
Yeah. You, uh...

215
00:13:01,514 --> 00:13:03,415
You have dealt
with a god or two.

216
00:13:05,318 --> 00:13:06,581
Yep.

217
00:13:07,086 --> 00:13:08,247
I wanna be human.

218
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:11,617
Like you.

219
00:13:12,525 --> 00:13:13,618
Excuse me?

220
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:17,256
I worship you, Julia.

221
00:13:19,265 --> 00:13:21,477
How did you do it, though? Because
that's the part that I couldn't quite see.

222
00:13:21,501 --> 00:13:23,970
There's some kind of cloak
around the whole process.

223
00:13:24,904 --> 00:13:28,500
Uh, rumor is it has
something to do with a book.

224
00:13:28,608 --> 00:13:31,669
Yeah, okay, I'm gonna
need just a few more details.

225
00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:34,280
I don't know.
Starting with "Why?"

226
00:13:34,347 --> 00:13:37,340
Do I want to be
human? Oh, it's simple.

227
00:13:37,450 --> 00:13:39,749
So, I'm the Goddess
of Melody, right?

228
00:13:39,852 --> 00:13:43,118
But did you know that we
can't actually feel music?

229
00:13:43,189 --> 00:13:47,752
Like, we understand it, we can
tell the good from the bad. Sort of.

230
00:13:47,927 --> 00:13:51,455
So you want to be human
so you can do karaoke.

231
00:13:52,532 --> 00:13:56,367
I know that it sounds
like hubris itself, but...

232
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:59,536
I think I could be a rock star.

233
00:14:00,039 --> 00:14:03,305
I mean, I pretty much know the
gig, right? They all prayed to me.

234
00:14:03,376 --> 00:14:07,575
Except for Amy Winehouse, okay?
Look how that one turned out. Poor thing.

235
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,978
Any other questions?

236
00:14:09,716 --> 00:14:10,716
Oh, boy.

237
00:14:42,582 --> 00:14:44,346
This is amazing.

238
00:14:49,589 --> 00:14:50,589
Careful.

239
00:14:50,690 --> 00:14:51,690
Whoa!

240
00:14:53,593 --> 00:14:55,357
Real world isn't quite gone.

241
00:15:04,370 --> 00:15:05,370
Oh.

242
00:15:06,038 --> 00:15:07,768
This is what my neck feels like.

243
00:15:11,944 --> 00:15:15,278
Come on. The
depository. Come on.

244
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:32,622
Welcome. KADY: H... Hi.

245
00:15:33,566 --> 00:15:35,125
Oh.

246
00:15:35,234 --> 00:15:39,433
We're looking for a depository
that was, uh... It was over there.

247
00:15:39,806 --> 00:15:40,933
Eat up.

248
00:15:41,507 --> 00:15:45,239
Yeah, in a sec, but if you
know where the depository is...

249
00:15:45,311 --> 00:15:47,803
Nobody knows where
anything is in the Realm.

250
00:15:47,914 --> 00:15:49,041
Except for the Emperor.

251
00:15:49,115 --> 00:15:52,142
Dear God. This is strange.

